        "body": "**Yes, it works.** @jessiejc23 \r\n\r\nHowever, you'll need to type five more characters `math.` to use the library (e.g. `math.pi` instead of `pi`), which decreases the coding speed significantly.\r\n\r\nYou can see **_the typing speed, instead of the code style, is the major limitation_**: www.youtube.com/watch?v=kBGhWRW39Zo\r\n\r\nAfter all, the codes are not written to be read. On the micro:bit chip, you just type as few characters as possible to run the expected codes so it's unnecessary to keep good coding style or make comments."
